# TOOLS.md - DevClaw Tool Reference

Complete parameter reference for all DevClaw tools.

## Worker Lifecycle

### work_start

Pick up a task from the issue queue. Handles label transition, level assignment, session creation, dispatch, and audit.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug (e.g. 'my-webapp') |
| issueId | number | no | Issue ID. If omitted, picks next by priority |
| role | string | no | Worker role. Auto-detected from label if omitted |
| level | string | no | Worker level (junior/medior/senior). Auto-detected if omitted |

### work_finish

Complete a task. Handles label transition, state update, issue close/reopen, notifications, and audit logging.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| role | string | yes | Worker role (developer/tester/reviewer/architect) |
| result | string | yes | Completion result: done, pass, fail, refine, blocked, approve, reject |
| summary | string | no | Brief summary of what was done |
| prUrl | string | no | PR/MR URL (auto-detected if omitted) |

## Task Management

### task_create

Create a new task (issue) in the project's issue tracker. Always creates in "Planning" unless the user explicitly asks to start work immediately.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| title | string | yes | Short, descriptive issue title |
| description | string | no | Full issue body in markdown |
| label | string | no | State label. Defaults to "Planning" |
| assignees | string[] | no | GitHub/GitLab usernames to assign |
| pickup | boolean | no | If true, immediately pick up for DEV after creation |

### task_update

Change issue state and/or role:level assignment.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| issueId | number | yes | Issue ID to update |
| state | string | no | New state label |
| level | string | no | Override the role:level assignment |
| reason | string | no | Audit log reason for the change |

### task_comment

Add a comment to an issue. Use for review feedback, implementation notes, or discussion.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| issueId | number | yes | Issue ID to comment on |
| body | string | yes | Comment body in markdown |
| authorRole | string | no | Role attribution (developer/tester/reviewer/architect/orchestrator) |

### task_edit_body

Update issue title and/or description. Only allowed in the initial workflow state (e.g. "Planning").

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| issueId | number | yes | Issue ID to edit |
| title | string | no | New title |
| body | string | no | New body/description |
| reason | string | no | Why the edit was made (for audit trail) |
| addComment | boolean | no | Post an auto-comment noting the edit (default: true) |

## Operations

### tasks_status

Full project dashboard: issues waiting for input (hold), work in progress (active), and queued for work (queue) — all with issue details.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | no | Project slug. Omit for all projects |

### task_list

Browse issues for a project by workflow state. Use for detailed issue browsing and search.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| stateType | string | no | Filter: queue, active, hold, terminal, or all (default: all non-terminal) |
| label | string | no | Specific state label (e.g. "Planning", "Done"). Overrides stateType |
| search | string | no | Text search in issue titles (case-insensitive) |
| limit | number | no | Max issues per state (default: 20) |

### health

Scan worker health across projects. Detects zombies, stale workers, orphaned state.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | no | Project slug. Omit for all projects |
| fix | boolean | no | Apply fixes for detected issues (default: false, read-only) |

### research_task

Spawn an architect to research a design/architecture problem. Creates a "To Research" issue and dispatches an architect worker.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectSlug | string | yes | Project slug |
| title | string | yes | Research title |
| description | string | yes | Detailed background context |
| focusAreas | string[] | no | Specific areas to investigate |
| complexity | string | no | simple, medium (default), or complex |
| dryRun | boolean | no | Preview without executing (default: false) |

## Setup & Configuration

### onboard

Start DevClaw onboarding workflow. Returns step-by-step guidance.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| mode | string | no | "first-run" or "reconfigure". Auto-detected if omitted |

### setup

Execute DevClaw setup. Creates AGENTS.md, HEARTBEAT.md, data directories, and model config.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| newAgentName | string | no | Create a new agent. Omit to configure current workspace |
| channelBinding | string | no | Channel to bind: "telegram" or "whatsapp" (with newAgentName only) |
| migrateFrom | string | no | Agent ID to migrate channel binding from |
| models | object | no | Model overrides per role and level |
| projectExecution | string | no | "parallel" (default) or "sequential" |

### autoconfigure_models

Automatically discover authenticated models and assign them to DevClaw roles.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| preferProvider | string | no | Prefer models from this provider (e.g. 'anthropic', 'openai') |

### project_register

Register a new project with DevClaw. Creates state labels, scaffolds role files, adds to projects.json.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| projectGroupId | string | yes | Project group ID (e.g. Telegram group ID) |
| name | string | yes | Short project name |
| repo | string | yes | Path to git repo |
| baseBranch | string | yes | Base branch for development |
| channel | string | no | Channel type (default: "telegram") |
| groupName | string | no | Group display name |
| deployBranch | string | no | Branch that triggers deployment (default: baseBranch) |
| deployUrl | string | no | Deployment URL |
| roleExecution | string | no | "parallel" (default) or "sequential" |

### workflow_guide

Reference guide for editing workflow.yaml. Call BEFORE making any workflow config changes.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| topic | string | no | Narrow to: overview, states, roles, review, testing, timeouts, or overrides |
